Program: Discovery
Title: Life on Mars
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwlm
Last Broadcast Date: 05 February 1996
Life on Mars, in this case the form of bacteria buried beneath the surface of the planet. Scientists are meeting to debate what kind of life is on Mars and whether a comet brought life to the Earth. Also in the programme, what the Hubble telescope saw on Betelgeuse and table-top terawatt lasers. Presenter: Martin Redfern. Producer: Ruth Linton. Show less